{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Eudi Wallet Kit supports custom key management through the implementation of SecureArea and SecureKeyStorage protocols. This document details the process of integrating custom key management with the library."}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"EudiWalletKit"}],"role":"article","title":"Custom key management"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EudiWalletKit\/documentation\/EudiWalletKit\/GetStarted","doc:\/\/EudiWalletKit\/documentation\/EudiWalletKit\/ManageDocuments","doc:\/\/EudiWalletKit\/documentation\/EudiWalletKit\/PresentationService","doc:\/\/EudiWalletKit\/documentation\/EudiWalletKit\/WalletUI"],"title":"Essentials","generated":true}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/eudiwalletkit\/secureareas"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/EudiWalletKit\/documentation\/EudiWalletKit\/SecureAreas"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Secure-areas","text":"Secure areas"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The wallet developer can customize cryptographic key operations by passing "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/eu-digital-identity-wallet.github.io\/eudi-lib-ios-iso18013-data-model\/documentation\/mdocdatamodel18013\/securearea"},{"type":"text","text":" instances to the wallet. In the absence of custom instances, the wallet kit automatically generates "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/eu-digital-identity-wallet.github.io\/eudi-lib-ios-iso18013-security\/documentation\/mdocsecurity18013\/secureenclavesecurearea"},{"type":"text","text":" (default) and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/eu-digital-identity-wallet.github.io\/eudi-lib-ios-iso18013-security\/documentation\/mdocsecurity18013\/softwaresecurearea"},{"type":"text","text":" secure areas."}]},{"type":"pa